d      +47         Share    Q&A Find answers to frequently asked questions about the song and explore its deeper meaning Ask a question What did Sabrina Carpenter say about "Taste"?  Genius Answer 1 contributor So, ‘Taste’ is one of my favorite songs off the album and it says a lot about me and a lot about other people. I think it’s sort of poking fun of myself a little bit for my mistakes and also poking fun at the, kind of like, facepalm that is life and relationship and the, sort of, situations that it puts you in, um, and it’s just making lighthearted fun at the whole concept of, you know, people that you’ve been with moving on to other people, and, you know, I think it’s a very human thing but it’s certainly fun.  —via Kiss 108  Behind The Scenes  Genius Answer 1 contributor      Official Lyric Video  Genius Answer 1 contributor      Teaser  How did the song perform commercially?  Who produced “Taste” by Sabrina Carpenter?  When did Sabrina Carpenter release “Taste”?  Who wrote “Taste” by Sabrina Carpenter?     Short n’ Sweet (Bonus Track)    (2024) Sabrina Carpenter 1. Taste 2. Please Please Please 3. Good Graces 4. Sharpest Tool 5. Coincidence 6. Bed Chem 7. Espresso 8. Dumb & Poetic 9. Slim Pickins 10. Juno 11. Lie To Girls 12. Don’t Smile 13. Needless To Say Expand      Credits Producers John Ryan , Ian Kirkpatrick & Julian Bunetta Writers Sabrina Carpenter , John Ryan , Julia Michaels , Amy Allen & Ian Kirkpatrick Mixed At MixStar Studios Publisher Sabalicious Songs , Universal Music Group , Don Wyan Music , Big Family Music , Hipgnosis Songs , Good Deal Publishing , Kenny + Betty Tunes , Warner/Chappell , Buckley Tenenbaum Publishing & Warner-Tamerlane Publishing Corp. Video Executive Producer Nathan Scherrer Video Producer Collin Druz , Aiden Magarian & Nathan Scherrer Video Commissioner Steve Gottlieb Video Production Company Freenjoy Video Director Of Photography Scott Cunningham Video Production Designer Grant Armstrong Video Editor Emile Doucette Vid